她昨天出了远门 没睡好
She traveled yesterday. She slept in a strange bed.

868
00:48:23,280 --> 00:48:25,360
给她个机会
Give her a chance.

869
00:48:27,880 --> 00:48:30,200
她6岁就看过奇默的书
At six years old, she read Zimmer.

870
00:48:31,440 --> 00:48:32,600
厉害
Outstanding.

871
00:48:33,440 --> 00:48:35,680
她看懂了多少
How much did she comprehend?

872
00:48:37,600 --> 00:48:38,880
玛丽
So, Mary...

873
00:48:39,920 --> 00:48:42,730
你在看我们的小问题
I see you're looking at our little problem.

874
00:48:43,040 --> 00:48:45,240
小问题? 这是个大问题
Little? It's big.

875
00:48:46,000 --> 00:48:47,000
是啊
Yeah.

876
00:48:53,240 --> 00:48:54,960
你怎么突然这么生气
Why are you so mad all of a sudden?

877
00:48:55,160 --> 00:48:57,280
我不是生气 是恼火
I'm not mad. I'm annoyed.

878
00:48:57,440 --> 00:48:58,480
不是恼火你
Not with you, dear.

879
00:48:58,560 --> 00:49:00,840
是恼火那个傲慢的尚克兰
With that pompous ass, Shankland.

880
00:49:01,040 --> 00:49:02,760
我们还没进去
I knew that guy was gonna have a beard

881
00:49:02,840 --> 00:49:04,490
就知道他是个大胡子
before we even went in there.

882
00:49:04,640 --> 00:49:06,640
数学老师都喜欢长胡子
Math teachers like to grow beards.

883
00:49:06,800 --> 00:49:09,160
我当初就不该答应这事
I should never have agreed to this in the first place.

884
00:49:09,320 --> 00:49:10,680
他真的指望你
Did he really expect you

885
00:49:10,800 --> 00:49:12,210
随随便便就能解析
to just walk in and be able to dissect...

886
00:49:12,240 --> 00:49:14,280
某个随机的复杂难题
some random, massive problem?

887
00:49:14,440 --> 00:49:17,480
我看也没什么可解析的
Not much to dissect, if you ask me.

888
00:49:17,680 --> 00:49:19,040
为什么这么说
Why do you say that?

889
00:49:19,120 --> 00:49:20,120
题错了
It was wrong.

890
00:49:21,120 --> 00:49:22,200
什么
What?

